8d0d8c61-1dd9-4338-9afe-1aa4efa9a796.do_description: To make the output, you have to... surround the middle point of the intersection with a 3x3 yellow border, leaving the central block in its original color.
8d0d8c61-1dd9-4338-9afe-1aa4efa9a796.grid_description: The output grid size... is identical to the input grid.
8d0d8c61-1dd9-4338-9afe-1aa4efa9a796.see_description: In the input, you should see... two intersecting lines of different colors

9e1011a8-19d2-4885-99b2-ae0b7d9b6d62.do_description: To make the output, you have to...create a yellow square around the point where the two lines meet.
9e1011a8-19d2-4885-99b2-ae0b7d9b6d62.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same.
9e1011a8-19d2-4885-99b2-ae0b7d9b6d62.see_description: In the input, you should see...two different color lines that cross.

dd43de0f-cb2a-41e8-9e12-85f5494ba917.do_description: To make the output, you have to... draw a 3x3 square around the point that the lines intersect (but make sure the exact point they meet stays the original color (for instance, if it is a red line crossing over a green line, draw a 3x3 square surrounding the point they cross over, but make sure the red point is still visible).
dd43de0f-cb2a-41e8-9e12-85f5494ba917.grid_description: The output grid size... the same size as the input grid.
dd43de0f-cb2a-41e8-9e12-85f5494ba917.see_description: In the input, you should see... two different color lines intersecting.
